16
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,472
Of course,
not everyone who reads this book

17
00:00:44,577 --> 00:00:47,273
fels guilt over the bad things they do.

18
00:00:47,347 --> 00:00:49,907
But Bre Van De Kamp did.

19
00:00:50,016 --> 00:00:54,282
In fact, Bre had spent
most of her life feling guilty.

20
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:58,881
As a child, she felt guilty
about not getting straight As.

21
00:01:00,126 --> 00:01:04,790
As a tenager, she felt guilty about
letting her boyfriend go to second base.

22
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:09,698
As a newlywed, she felt guilty
about taking thre weks

23
00:01:09,769 --> 00:01:12,169
to get out her thank-you cards.

24
00:01:12,272 --> 00:01:14,763
But she knew
the transgressions of her past

25
00:01:14,874 --> 00:01:18,469
were nothing compared with
the sin she was about to commit.

26
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:21,274
Can't we just tell the police
it was an accident?

27
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,872
This wasn't some simple D.U.I.

28
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:27,248
Not only was Andrew drinking,
he left the scene of the crime.

29
00:01:27,353 --> 00:01:30,254
- That makes it a hit-and-run.
- I could go to Canada.

30
00:01:30,356 --> 00:01:33,348
Till the statute of limitations is up.

31
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:36,861
You think Mom and Day will pay
for you to go moose hunting?

32
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:40,024
If Carlos' mother dies,
there is no statute of limitations.

33
00:01:40,166 --> 00:01:41,895
- Because it's murder.
- Shut up!

34
00:01:41,968 --> 00:01:46,132
- You shut up.
- It was an accident!

35
00:01:48,007 --> 00:01:50,874
We have to get rid of the car.

36
00:01:57,350 --> 00:02:01,013
But we can't sell it. The police might
find it and there could be D.N.A.

37
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:03,021
We'll take it to a bad part of town,

38
00:02:03,089 --> 00:02:06,388
leave the keys in the ignition
and the doors unlocked.

39
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:09,155
If the police don't find it
we'll get the insurance

40
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:12,687
and if they do,
it wasn't in our possession.

41
00:02:12,765 --> 00:02:16,064
Anyone could have hit Mrs. Solis.

42
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:19,299
That sounds good.

43
00:02:19,405 --> 00:02:21,532
Bree, are you sure?

44
00:02:21,608 --> 00:02:25,135
Our son could spend the rest of his life
in jail. I won't allow that.

45
00:02:25,245 --> 00:02:28,703
Bre knew what
she was about to do was wrong.

46
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,316
But like most sinners, she would
worry about her guilt tomorrow.

47
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,080
