48
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,815
Everybody should go wash up.

49
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:39,216
We're having pancakes for breakfast.

50
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:25,200
Not since my own suicide

51
00:03:25,305 --> 00:03:29,105
had violence intruded upon
the serenity of life on Wisteria Lane

52
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:31,370
in such a conspicuous fashion.

53
00:03:31,444 --> 00:03:35,175
Nedless to say,
my friends attacked the problem head-on.

54
00:03:35,248 --> 00:03:39,514
Lynette brought the broom,
Susan brought the trash bags,

55
00:03:39,586 --> 00:03:42,885
and Bre brought
the industrial strength solvent.

56
00:03:42,956 --> 00:03:45,481
Whoo. That stuff is strong.

57
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:48,321
It has to be.
I don't want Gabrielle and Carlos

58
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:52,421
coming home to this ugly reminder
in front of their house.

59
00:03:52,532 --> 00:03:56,593
- Has anyone been over there?
- Julie and I went over this morning.

60
00:03:56,703 --> 00:04:00,730
- How's Juanita doing?
- She's in a coma.

61
00:04:00,807 --> 00:04:03,401
Nobody knows when
or even if she'll wake up.

62
00:04:03,509 --> 00:04:06,205
This is awful.
Carlos must be just devastated.

63
00:04:06,279 --> 00:04:09,407
I hope she wakes up
and tells us who was driving that car.

64
00:04:09,515 --> 00:04:12,040
We can only hope.

65
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:17,146
Slow down, you jerk!
This is a residential neighborhood!

66
00:04:18,658 --> 00:04:20,649
That's quite a pitching arm.

67
00:04:20,727 --> 00:04:25,164
I've got four kids. I was up all night
reading statistics online.

68
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:29,258
One out of every four traffic accidents
happens on residential streets.

69
00:04:29,335 --> 00:04:33,135
I hope whoever hit Juanita
gets put away for life.

70
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:35,969
Don't you think
that's a little bit extreme?

71
00:04:36,075 --> 00:04:40,034
An innocent woman gets hit by a car and
the driver takes off? It's not extreme.

72
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:50,017
You should go home and get some rest.
Eat something.

73
00:04:50,089 --> 00:04:53,650
You have messages from work.
Tanaka called. Said it was urgent.

74
00:04:53,726 --> 00:04:57,492
- I can stay here with your mother.
- I need to be here if she wakes up.

75
00:04:57,597 --> 00:05:00,157
You can't go on like this.

76
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:04,294
And what if she dies? People slip into
comas all the time and never come out.

77
00:05:04,370 --> 00:05:07,362
Don't say that.
We need to stay positive.

78
00:05:08,608 --> 00:05:11,338
- Mr. And Mrs. Solis.
- John.

79
00:05:13,713 --> 00:05:16,546
- Is it OK if I come in?
- Of course.

80
00:05:24,023 --> 00:05:27,618
Mr. Solis, I'm so sorry this happened.

81
00:05:27,694 --> 00:05:30,822
It means a lot that you came.

82
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:45,810
I think I'm gonna go down
to the chapel and pray.

83
00:05:45,878 --> 00:05:48,210
- You wanna come?
- Um...

84
00:05:48,314 --> 00:05:50,908
No. I think I will stay here with Mama.

85
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:58,748
- Is it all right if I come?
- Course.

86
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:01,190
We need all the prayers we can get.

87
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,435
Mrs. Solis,
it's time for her sponge bath.

88
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:16,337
Come again?

89
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:20,277
Sometimes family members prefer to
administer sponge baths themselves.

90
00:06:23,483 --> 00:06:24,848
I think I'll pass.

91
00:06:30,323 --> 00:06:32,223
Martha.

92
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:36,719
- Where's your purse?
- Over there. Why?

93
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:47,532
- What are you doing?
- Taking back the $40 you stole.

94
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:48,174
- Edie!
- I know you did it. Hand it over!

95
00:06:48,174 --> 00:06:50,438
- Edie!
- I know you did it. Hand it over!

96
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:53,410
I have taken nothing from your purse.

97
00:06:53,479 --> 00:06:57,472
If you're missing money, I'd ask one
of those men you parade through here.

98
00:06:58,951 --> 00:07:02,114
I am not going to apologize
for having a healthy sex life.

99
00:07:02,221 --> 00:07:04,781
Healthy? I'm going to
have to burn every sheet.

100
00:07:04,891 --> 00:07:08,952
- I want my money.
- I want those non-fat peach yogurts.

101
00:07:09,028 --> 00:07:11,588
They didn't just walk out of the fridge.

102
00:07:11,697 --> 00:07:15,133
You can deduct it from the $40
that you're going to give me now.

103
00:07:15,234 --> 00:07:18,226
You're my best friend.
Why would I steal from you?

104
00:07:18,337 --> 00:07:21,397
It's no secret that you've been having
financial problems.

105
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:24,942
- I hear you bitching to your bank.
- That's it.

106
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:27,706
I can put up with your debauchery
and food theft,

107
00:07:27,814 --> 00:07:29,714
but I will not tolerate spying.

108
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,841
- I want you out.
- You don't mean that.

109
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:35,580
Oh, yes, I do. I'm leaving tomorrow
to visit my sister for a few days.

110
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:37,987
I want you gone by the time I get back.

111
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:40,615
I'll do you one better.

112
00:07:42,061 --> 00:07:44,188
I will leave today.

113
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:58,804
I hope this works. My sleep cycle's
totally out of whack.

114
00:07:58,878 --> 00:08:02,405
I'm up all night,
then dozing off during the day.

115
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:05,144
Trust me. This will do the trick.

116
00:08:05,218 --> 00:08:08,619
In fact, you should be
feeling more relaxed already.

117
00:08:08,754 --> 00:08:12,485
- [Boys shout]
- You know, you're right.

118
00:08:12,558 --> 00:08:16,722
Boys, I can hear you out there!
Be quiet! Just sit there and color.

119
00:08:16,796 --> 00:08:20,493
- Now is not a good time to be moving.
- Sorry.

120
00:08:20,566 --> 00:08:23,296
Just block everything out

121
00:08:23,436 --> 00:08:26,200
and let it go.

122
00:08:26,305 --> 00:08:28,671
Imagine that you're in a forest.

123
00:08:28,741 --> 00:08:31,767
There's a babbling brook nearby.

124
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:36,042
And the wind is just coming
through the trees...

125
00:08:36,115 --> 00:08:37,673
- Mommy?
- Parker!

126
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:40,776
I don't know... Ow!
...what you think you're doing,

127
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:43,845
but put that back where it belongs.

128
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:50,160
Sorry.
You were saying something about wind.

129
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:53,424
I was just creating a soothing image.

130
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,194
[Boys shout]

131
00:08:55,301 --> 00:08:57,701
Oh, for the love of God.

132
00:08:58,638 --> 00:09:01,766
Knock it off, you little monsters.

133
00:09:04,310 --> 00:09:06,870
Mrs. Scavo, lie down.
We need to finish this.

134
00:09:06,946 --> 00:09:10,882
I'm on my last nerves,
so I'm gonna level with you here.

135
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:15,114
I've screwed up my entire system
by taking my kids' A.D.D. Medication.

136
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:20,681
Yeah, you heard me. I plan to stop.
But right now I need to sleep

137
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:25,163
and I need more than a few crappy
needles, so what have you got?

138
00:09:25,298 --> 00:09:27,459
I'm not licensed to write prescriptions.

139
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:31,401
- I know you're not.
- [Shouting continues]

140
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:42,139
This will put you right to sleep.
It's a very powerful herbal remedy.

141
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,478
Promise me you'll use it judiciously.

142
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:46,779
Sure. Whatever.

143
00:09:49,322 --> 00:09:50,983
Knock, knock!

144
00:09:51,090 --> 00:09:55,049
- Hey. Come on in.
- You're a mess.

145
00:09:55,127 --> 00:09:58,187
I'm tearing out the leaky pipes
in the upstairs bathroom.

146
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:03,459
- Wall-to-wall rotten wood.
- Sounds like a job.

147
00:10:03,569 --> 00:10:05,833
Julie said that you came by before.

148
00:10:05,905 --> 00:10:09,204
Um... yeah. Uh... I was thinking about

149
00:10:09,342 --> 00:10:13,335
driving up to the Germani vineyard
tomorrow for this wine tasting and...

150
00:10:13,412 --> 00:10:16,040
- What time should I be ready?
- About 6:00.

151
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:18,845
6:00 is good.

152
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:21,112
All right.

153
00:10:21,187 --> 00:10:25,317
I thought maybe afterwards we could have
a little dinner, maybe some dancing.

154
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:27,723
Sounds great.

155
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:31,126
Um... you do know that it's, like,
a two-hour drive up there.

156
00:10:31,197 --> 00:10:35,224
Isn't that kind of late
to be coming back?

157
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:39,134
I thought if worse came to worse
we could... grab a room.

158
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:41,469
Oh? Like a hotel room?

159
00:10:41,540 --> 00:10:45,032
- Yeah. As a last resort.
- Of course. Of course. Yes.

160
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:48,602
So maybe we should make a reservation.
You know, just in case.

161
00:10:48,681 --> 00:10:53,618
Yeah, I found some hotels online.
Let me get the print-out.

162
00:10:54,954 --> 00:10:58,219
Hey, Bongo. Come here.
Do you want a treat?

163
00:10:58,290 --> 00:11:01,418
- Where do you keep the dog biscuits?
- Sorry, what?

164
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:02,756
Oh, never mind.

165
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:05,854
We'll just find them ourselves, huh?

166
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:19,102
Sorry, I couldn't hear you.
What did you say?

167
00:11:20,312 --> 00:11:23,213
Nothing. It's not important.

168
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:25,375
[Phone rings]

169
00:11:25,484 --> 00:11:28,544
It's my tiler guy.
Here. See what looks good.

170
00:11:28,654 --> 00:11:30,884
Hey, Phil.

171
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:34,391
No, tomorrow morning
I'm making a lumber run. That's no good.

172
00:11:34,493 --> 00:11:37,291
No, I'm gone tomorrow night, too.

173
00:11:37,363 --> 00:11:41,732
- I could let him in.
- No, it's OK. Thanks.

174
00:11:41,834 --> 00:11:45,463
It's fine. Just give me the key.
I'll be around all day.

175
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,371
All right. Um... thanks.

176
00:11:48,441 --> 00:11:52,172
Phil, I'll give a key to my neighbor.
She'll be here to let you in.

177
00:12:01,153 --> 00:12:03,917
Like every city,
Fairview had a neighborhood

178
00:12:03,989 --> 00:12:06,048
that was less than desirable.

179
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:09,720
It was an accepted fact, anyone
who lingered there after midnight

180
00:12:09,795 --> 00:12:12,059
was usually up to no good.

181
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:19,095
Rex and Bre Van De Kamp
were no exception.

182
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:32,680
You really think this is gonna work?

183
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:35,482
This is an impoverished
neighborhood.

184
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:39,046
- Trust me. Somebody will steal the car.
- How can you be so sure?

185
00:12:39,191 --> 00:12:41,716
Because I have faith in the poor.

186
00:12:44,296 --> 00:12:48,630
[Paul] She's so beautiful.
I shot this last year on her birthday.

187
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:56,570
- How are you going to do it?
- I made contact with her at a bar.

188
00:12:56,642 --> 00:12:59,076
She thinks I'm a real-estate developer.

189
00:12:59,145 --> 00:13:02,410
- Is she going to suffer?
- No.

190
00:13:02,481 --> 00:13:05,814
Edie Britt will disappear
and you'll go back to your life.

191
00:13:05,885 --> 00:13:11,448
Before you do it, do you think you could
ask her why she sent this to my wife?

192
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:15,426
You can't think like that, Mr. Young.
You can't give in to your curiosity.

193
00:13:15,494 --> 00:13:19,794
Curiosity leads to guilt.
Guilt leads to talking.

194
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:22,026
Do you still have questions?

195
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:27,697
I want to be clear about something. If
I walk away with this cash, it's done.

196
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:29,798
No refunds. No buyer's remorse.

197
00:13:29,909 --> 00:13:32,434
I get it.

198
00:13:32,511 --> 00:13:35,446
We won't talk again,
so I'll ask one more time.

199
00:13:35,514 --> 00:13:37,675
Are you sure you want this?

200
00:13:38,851 --> 00:13:41,081
My wife is dead because of Edie Britt.

201
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:44,612
I absolutely want this.

202
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:53,487
You've been awfully quiet.

203
00:13:56,135 --> 00:14:00,196
I've just been thinking about the kids.

204
00:14:03,709 --> 00:14:06,200
They sure grew up quickly, didn't they?

205
00:14:06,278 --> 00:14:08,542
They sure did.

206
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:13,817
I told them when they were babies
that they shouldn't get bigger

207
00:14:13,886 --> 00:14:16,377
because they were so adorable.

208
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:21,315
- And we were so happy.
- Yeah, well...

209
00:14:21,393 --> 00:14:24,851
They sure didn't turn out
like we expected them to.

210
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:27,694
No. They didn't.

211
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,502
Oh, we could have been better parents.

212
00:14:30,502 --> 00:14:30,831
Oh, we could have been better parents.

213
00:14:30,903 --> 00:14:34,999
- We weren't that bad.
- We still have so much to teach them.

214
00:14:35,074 --> 00:14:38,168
We need to show Andrew
the enormity of what he's done.

215
00:14:38,244 --> 00:14:40,872
I suppose we could punish him.

216
00:14:40,946 --> 00:14:44,939
What's the appropriate punishment
for a child who drives over a woman?

217
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,814
I don't know.

218
00:14:49,121 --> 00:14:51,988
No matter how the kids turn out,
I still love them.

219
00:14:52,057 --> 00:14:54,525
Course you do.

220
00:14:54,593 --> 00:14:57,892
But I'll never forgive them
for growing up so quickly.

221
00:15:02,668 --> 00:15:05,398
Hey, look.

222
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:22,011
And I opened the cabinet
and there was all this money in it.

223
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:26,454
- There was wads of it.
- You're freaking out over cash?

224
00:15:26,558 --> 00:15:29,288
Realistically,
I've known this guy a few weeks.

225
00:15:29,361 --> 00:15:31,556
He could be a hit man for the mob.

226
00:15:31,630 --> 00:15:33,723
Then why are you going
on a trip with him?

227
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:35,596
I never get out of the house.

228
00:15:35,668 --> 00:15:39,832
If you need to freak out, remember that
you're spending the night with Mike.

229
00:15:39,905 --> 00:15:43,170
No man has seen you naked in years.
Except your doctor.

230
00:15:43,242 --> 00:15:45,870
And he retired.
I try not to take that personally.

231
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:48,573
You look old in that.

232
00:15:48,647 --> 00:15:51,013
Maybe I am being silly.

233
00:15:51,116 --> 00:15:54,381
But going to a hotel with a man
is a big deal to me.

234
00:15:54,486 --> 00:15:56,977
What if Mike is hiding something?

235
00:15:57,056 --> 00:15:59,923
- Like what?
- I don't know.

236
00:15:59,992 --> 00:16:03,359
- [Car horn]
- That's Dad. I gotta go.

237
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:07,523
Now, listen. No more freaking out.
I need this weekend to go well.

238
00:16:07,599 --> 00:16:11,501
- Why do you care so much?
- I'm gonna have a husband some day.

239
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:14,835
I really don't want you living with us.

240
00:16:19,445 --> 00:16:22,437
- [Bree] Are the lady fingers OK?
- They're terrific.

241
00:16:22,514 --> 00:16:24,914
We just appreciate you all stopping by.

242
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,452
We just wanted you to know
how much we care.

243
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:31,148
So have the police
come up with any leads?

244
00:16:31,223 --> 00:16:34,852
Not really. They'll be able to determine
the make and model of the car,

245
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:38,293
but without any eyewitnesses,
no one seems very optimistic.

246
00:16:38,364 --> 00:16:41,128
Is there any good news about Juanita?

247
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:44,862
No change. All we can do
is wait and hope for the best.

248
00:16:46,205 --> 00:16:49,868
- We put her on our prayer list.
- That's very sweet. Thank you.

249
00:16:49,942 --> 00:16:54,902
It must really help
during times like these, having kids.

250
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,881
Yeah. They're a blessing.

251
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:00,851
Children make everything worthwhile.

252
00:17:02,454 --> 00:17:05,480
You guys are the future. Legacy.

253
00:17:05,624 --> 00:17:07,319
Thanks.

254
00:17:07,393 --> 00:17:10,760
After we're all dead, you'll be
the only ones left to carry on.

255
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:15,697
Gabrielle and I
are about to start a family.

256
00:17:15,768 --> 00:17:18,066
Oh! Hey, that's great!

257
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:21,606
- When did you decide this?
- It's a fairly recent development.

258
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:26,207
I see.

259
00:17:26,278 --> 00:17:30,044
- We'll talk about this later.
- Face it. We're shallow people.

260
00:17:30,149 --> 00:17:33,141
Can our lives have any meaning
if all we do is buy stuff?

261
00:17:33,285 --> 00:17:36,083
- That depends on what we buy.
- I want a child.

262
00:17:36,188 --> 00:17:39,624
In case you've forgotten,
we made a deal. No kids.

263
00:17:39,691 --> 00:17:44,287
- Deals were meant to be renegotiated.
- We're not negotiating my uterus.

264
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:47,263
- We should probably be going.
- Yeah.

265
00:17:47,366 --> 00:17:49,561
Thank you so much.

266
00:17:50,769 --> 00:17:54,102
- That was weird.
- I feel awful for Carlos.

267
00:17:54,173 --> 00:17:58,075
That talk about children
is obviously coming from his grief.

268
00:17:58,143 --> 00:18:00,270
Whatever. I'm off the hook.

269
00:18:08,353 --> 00:18:11,015
A weary Lynette drank her potent tea

270
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:15,151
in hopes of finally finding the slep
that had eluded her.

271
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:19,993
Unfortunately for Lynette,
there would be no rest for the weary.

272
00:18:20,099 --> 00:18:23,000
- [Doorbell]
- Go to hell.

273
00:18:23,068 --> 00:18:26,629
- [Doorbell rings several times]
- Go to hell, go to hell.

274
00:18:26,705 --> 00:18:28,764
[Urgent knocking]

275
00:18:35,714 --> 00:18:39,480
Sorry we're late. Kenny Lipman
couldn't find his neckerchief.

276
00:18:39,585 --> 00:18:42,349
Lori Jean, the Scout meeting is today?

277
00:18:48,527 --> 00:18:50,722
- Mommy!
- What? Oh. Right.

278
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:54,493
OK. Boys.
This knot is called the bowline.

279
00:18:54,566 --> 00:18:58,297
It is a remarkably useful knot.
Now, pick up your ropes.

280
00:18:58,370 --> 00:19:01,100
First we cross this end over here

281
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:04,835
and then we make a loop
and then another loop

282
00:19:04,943 --> 00:19:09,346
and then you sort of pull it through,
I'm guessing,

283
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:12,315
and then you just... Ready?
...yank it taut.

284
00:19:14,486 --> 00:19:16,920
Mommy, that doesn't look like
the picture.

285
00:19:18,257 --> 00:19:21,021
You're never gonna be a sailor.
What do you care?

286
00:19:21,126 --> 00:19:23,686
OK, everybody. Let's just take a break.

287
00:19:25,531 --> 00:19:27,499
Thanks.

288
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:44,613
OK. It's all up there.
Can I get a signature?

289
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,345
- Oh, course.
- Thank you very much.

290
00:19:49,421 --> 00:19:52,219
- There you go. Have a nice weekend.
- You too, lady.

291
00:20:19,251 --> 00:20:21,515
[Door slams shut]

292
00:20:36,835 --> 00:20:39,497
- [Knocking]
- [Man] Hey, ma'am!

293
00:20:39,605 --> 00:20:43,905
Are you still here?
I forgot to give you a receipt.

294
00:20:44,009 --> 00:20:46,409
Ma'am?

295
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,760
Oh...

296
00:21:15,741 --> 00:21:18,005
Hello!

297
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:23,908
I need help! I'm up here!
I'm trapped in the floor! Hello!

298
00:21:25,917 --> 00:21:29,114
If you came in here to judge me,
you can just leave.

299
00:21:30,355 --> 00:21:33,256
Wait! Wait, no! Wait. Don't go.

300
00:21:33,325 --> 00:21:36,488
I have an idea. Here.

301
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:38,791
Here. Grab the towel, Bongo.

302
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:41,128
Come on. Grab the other end. Good boy.

303
00:21:41,199 --> 00:21:45,101
That's it. Get the other end.
Come on, Bongo. Pull the other end.

304
00:21:45,170 --> 00:21:48,799
Come on, Bongo. What are you doing?
Bongo, over here.

305
00:21:48,874 --> 00:21:55,040
Bongo? Oh! Oh! Don't do that! Oh, Bongo!

306
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,048
While Susan remained hopelessly stuck,

307
00:21:56,048 --> 00:21:57,811
While Susan remained hopelessly stuck,

308
00:21:57,883 --> 00:22:00,317
Gabrielle was moving
to confront the issue

309
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:02,785
of her young lover's
restless conscience.

310
00:22:02,921 --> 00:22:06,618
- Nobody's home.
- I know. I came to talk to you.

311
00:22:06,692 --> 00:22:09,422
- But she would ned to be discret.
- Keep working.

312
00:22:11,096 --> 00:22:13,758
What were you thinking
showing up at the hospital?

313
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,232
I had to see if she was OK.

314
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,530
You need to keep
a low profile right now.

315
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:22,874
Look, you and I are finished.

316
00:22:22,941 --> 00:22:25,375
From now on, I'm sticking with Danielle.

317
00:22:25,444 --> 00:22:28,709
- Why would you say that?
- I hate myself for what we did.

318
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:31,874
I can't sleep at night.
We've got to make a clean break.

319
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:35,613
We weren't driving the car. We didn't
chase Juanita into the street.

320
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:38,212
She was there
because we were having an affair.

321
00:22:38,323 --> 00:22:43,022
Between you and Carlos! Listen to me.
You didn't do anything wrong.

322
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:47,624
- That's not what Father Crowley thinks.
- What?

323
00:22:47,766 --> 00:22:50,394
I went to confession.

324
00:22:52,637 --> 00:22:56,368
Have you lost your mind?
What did you tell him?

325
00:22:56,441 --> 00:22:59,808
- Everything.
- Including...

326
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:02,778
in the alley? Behind the truck stop?

327
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:05,509
- Everything.
- Damn you!

328
00:23:15,093 --> 00:23:19,792
What is wrong with you? Lassie would
have had a fire truck here by now.

329
00:23:19,898 --> 00:23:22,458
You stupid dog.

330
00:23:22,567 --> 00:23:26,833
Good boy, Bongo! Run, Bongo, run!
Go get help!

331
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,270
Oh!

332
00:23:40,118 --> 00:23:45,317
Andrew, um... I know the last few days
have been stressful

333
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:48,393
and if you ever need
to talk to anybody...

334
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:52,294
I know. You and Dad are here for me.

335
00:23:52,397 --> 00:23:55,457
Actually, I was thinking
you could talk to a professional.

336
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:57,592
A shrink?

337
00:23:59,638 --> 00:24:02,129
- You think I'm crazy?
- Course not.

338
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:05,698
It's just that the accident probably
stirred up a lot of emotions.

339
00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:11,181
It would be normal for you to be feeling
confused or depressed or shamed.

340
00:24:12,184 --> 00:24:14,880
I'm cool. Really.

341
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:19,356
You put a woman into a coma. Surely
that arouses some kind of emotion.

342
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:22,222
Yeah, well, it doesn't.

343
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:28,189
- If you'll excuse me.
- No! Not until you tell me.

344
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:31,827
- Why do you care?
- I need to know you're not a monster.

345
00:24:33,538 --> 00:24:36,996
- You want to know how I feel?
- Yeah.

346
00:24:37,108 --> 00:24:39,235
I feel bad that she got hurt.

347
00:24:39,377 --> 00:24:41,572
But I also feel bad
that my car got dinged

348
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:45,275
because somebody didn't have the sense
to look both ways.

349
00:24:45,350 --> 00:24:48,842
And I feel bad that now I'm gonna
have to ride my bike to school.

350
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:55,084
Andrew, you almost killed
another human being.

351
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:59,153
She's an old lady, OK?
She's lived her life.

352
00:24:59,231 --> 00:25:02,428
I have my whole life ahead of me
and now it might be screwed up.

353
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:07,461
- That's what you should worry about.
- You don't seem to have a soul.

354
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:13,072
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't call the police.

355
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:17,137
Because I'm your son.
That would make you the monster.

356
00:25:30,562 --> 00:25:32,393
Hey, buddy.

357
00:25:40,705 --> 00:25:45,039
- Susan, is that you?
- Mike? I'm upstairs. Sorta.

358
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:48,238
[Laughs] Hang on. I'll be right up.

359
00:25:56,821 --> 00:26:02,987
- What happened?
- This bird flew in your bathroom window

360
00:26:03,094 --> 00:26:07,827
and I tried to save it but uh...
it died.

361
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:11,528
- I don't think that's what happened.
- I don't think so either.

362
00:26:12,837 --> 00:26:15,305
- Come here.
- Help me get out of here please.

363
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:22,703
Oh! Thank you.

364
00:26:22,847 --> 00:26:27,216
Oh. You have no idea what that was like.

365
00:26:30,288 --> 00:26:33,951
- You went through my cabinets?
- What?

366
00:26:34,025 --> 00:26:37,483
- Oh, I can explain that.
- Get out of my house.

367
00:26:37,562 --> 00:26:41,794
- Mike...
- Get out.

368
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:14,025
- Hello there!
- Good afternoon.

369
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:20,003
Oh! Well, isn't this
just as pretty as a picture book?

370
00:27:20,105 --> 00:27:23,939
The plan is to put in a small condo.

371
00:27:24,009 --> 00:27:27,035
You want to make some money
or pussyfoot around?

372
00:27:27,145 --> 00:27:30,911
- What do you suggest?
- I'm thinking strip mall.

373
00:27:31,016 --> 00:27:33,541
I've run some numbers.

374
00:27:38,423 --> 00:27:41,392
- Nice stationery.
- Oh, it's stolen.

375
00:27:43,695 --> 00:27:45,720
What do you mean?

376
00:27:45,797 --> 00:27:49,096
After my house burned down,
I was staying with Martha Huber.

377
00:27:49,234 --> 00:27:51,600
That is until
the old troll threw me out.

378
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:55,436
I'd steal her stuff, she'd steal mine.
It's the circle of life.

379
00:27:56,641 --> 00:27:59,371
So this paper is hers?

380
00:27:59,444 --> 00:28:01,412
Oh, God, yes.

381
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,548
[Children make noise]

382
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:15,951
No, Tom, you can't do this to me.

383
00:28:16,094 --> 00:28:19,928
I need you home!
Boys, stop it! I am on the phone!

384
00:28:19,998 --> 00:28:24,901
Yeah, I realize it's not your fault
that the meeting got postponed

385
00:28:25,003 --> 00:28:27,563
but you promised you'd be back tonight.

386
00:28:27,672 --> 00:28:30,539
- Mom!
- I gotta go.

387
00:28:30,608 --> 00:28:33,406
The kids are... Yeah.

388
00:28:33,511 --> 00:28:37,880
I know you're sorry. Will you try
and get back as soon as you can?

389
00:28:37,949 --> 00:28:40,144
OK. Bye.

390
00:28:40,251 --> 00:28:44,085
Boys, would you please, please stop it?

391
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:49,226
Really. Mommy's got a headache, OK?
Just...

392
00:28:50,195 --> 00:28:53,096
♪ Dappled and drowsy
and ready to slep...

393
00:28:53,164 --> 00:28:56,156
Turn that damn thing off!

394
00:28:56,234 --> 00:29:00,364
What's the matter with you?
Why won't you listen to me?

395
00:29:00,438 --> 00:29:03,532
♪ All is groovy

396
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:06,308
[screams]

397
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:08,470
[59th Stret Bridge Song continues]

398
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:38,804
♪ Slow down, you move too fast

399
00:29:38,877 --> 00:29:42,643
♪ You've got to make the morning last

400
00:29:42,747 --> 00:29:46,114
♪ Just kicking down the cobbled stones

401
00:29:46,184 --> 00:29:50,177
♪ Looking for fun and feling groovy ♪

402
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:10,270
What?

403
00:30:10,341 --> 00:30:13,367
I just came over to say I'm sorry.

404
00:30:13,444 --> 00:30:15,503
And I'll pay for all the damage.

405
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:17,707
Don't worry about it.

406
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:20,182
Well... So...

407
00:30:20,285 --> 00:30:22,810
In your mind, is the date off?

408
00:30:22,887 --> 00:30:25,879
You snooped around my house
and went through my stuff.

409
00:30:25,990 --> 00:30:28,390
Yeah. That's pretty much a deal breaker.

410
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:33,396
I started snooping around because
I found all that money by accident.

411
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:37,093
Then I found a gun.

412
00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:39,659
- Are you a drug dealer?
- Is that what you think?

413
00:30:39,737 --> 00:30:44,003
I wouldn't know because you never
let me in. You're completely walled off.

414
00:30:44,075 --> 00:30:46,976
I have a gun for protection
and cash for emergencies.

415
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:49,878
I'm a good guy, Susan,
and you should know that.

416
00:30:49,948 --> 00:30:52,678
I'm not obligated to share
every little detail...

417
00:30:52,750 --> 00:30:56,242
Every little detail is one thing,
weird secrets is another.

418
00:30:56,354 --> 00:30:59,118
- You don't trust me.
- Maybe we shouldn't be dating.

419
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:01,420
Maybe we shouldn't.

420
00:31:01,492 --> 00:31:04,825
- Do you mean that?
- Yeah.

421
00:31:04,896 --> 00:31:08,388
I hope your little secret
keeps you warm at night

422
00:31:08,466 --> 00:31:12,527
because you're throwing something
really great away to protect it.

423
00:31:21,279 --> 00:31:24,806
Oh, Susan!
You gotta take my kids for a while.

424
00:31:24,916 --> 00:31:28,682
- This really isn't a good time.
- I'm sorry but I can't do this.

425
00:31:28,753 --> 00:31:32,245
It's too much.
Boys, you stay with your Aunt Susan.

426
00:31:32,357 --> 00:31:34,222
Yay!

427
00:31:34,292 --> 00:31:37,489
Lynette, when are you coming back?

428
00:31:38,630 --> 00:31:40,723
Lynette!

429
00:31:44,068 --> 00:31:46,263
Lynette!

430
00:32:01,019 --> 00:32:02,953
She's gotta be close.

431
00:32:03,021 --> 00:32:05,421
I hope the kids
aren't too much for Danielle.

432
00:32:05,490 --> 00:32:08,789
She'll be fine. What do you think
is happening with Lynette?

433
00:32:08,860 --> 00:32:12,318
I don't know. But I'm scared.
Something's very, very wrong.

434
00:32:26,711 --> 00:32:28,770
Lynette? Honey?

435
00:32:28,846 --> 00:32:31,280
Are you OK?

436
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:40,116
Father. I'm so glad you could come
and pray for Mama.

437
00:32:40,224 --> 00:32:43,022
- Please, sit.
- Thank you, Gabrielle.

438
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:55,270
Since you're here. There's something
I've always wondered about.

439
00:32:55,373 --> 00:32:58,206
That whole thing about priests

440
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:01,642
not being allowed to repeat
what they hear in confessions.

441
00:33:01,713 --> 00:33:05,114
Is that a hard rule
or just a general guideline?

442
00:33:05,249 --> 00:33:07,843
Rest assured,
everyone's secrets are safe.

443
00:33:07,952 --> 00:33:10,284
That's good to hear.

444
00:33:10,355 --> 00:33:13,051
I'll keep yours too if you want to talk.

445
00:33:13,157 --> 00:33:17,787
Me? No, no.
Confession's not really my thing.

446
00:33:17,862 --> 00:33:19,955
That's a shame.

447
00:33:23,968 --> 00:33:26,664
You can stop condemning me
with your eyes.

448
00:33:28,806 --> 00:33:30,933
Right now.

449
00:33:32,777 --> 00:33:35,541
I know you know about the affair.

450
00:33:35,646 --> 00:33:37,876
But you know nothing about my life.

451
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:42,877
It's not even an issue any more.
John and I are finished.

452
00:33:42,987 --> 00:33:45,148
Gabrielle, the Church is clear on this.

453
00:33:45,223 --> 00:33:48,818
If you commit a mortal sin
and you die without repenting,

454
00:33:48,893 --> 00:33:50,622
you go to hell.

455
00:33:50,728 --> 00:33:53,026
Well, aren't you just a ball of fun?

456
00:33:57,235 --> 00:34:01,001
So if I confess,
it'll clean the slate, right?

457
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:05,202
Not only that. If you want God's
forgiveness you have to be truly sorry

458
00:34:05,276 --> 00:34:07,801
and promise not to commit the sin again.

459
00:34:07,912 --> 00:34:11,780
So what happens if I repent later?

460
00:34:11,849 --> 00:34:13,908
Like, say, when I'm 75?

461
00:34:14,018 --> 00:34:16,851
What if you die before then?

462
00:34:16,988 --> 00:34:20,822
Let's say I don't die?
I do yoga. I eat well.

463
00:34:20,925 --> 00:34:23,758
If I wait,
does my repenting still count?

464
00:34:23,861 --> 00:34:25,692
If you mean it, yes.

465
00:34:26,631 --> 00:34:30,897
Thank you, Father Crowley.
You have been a tremendous comfort.

466
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:35,304
Um... I will let you do your thing.

467
00:34:35,406 --> 00:34:38,204
Gabrielle.

468
00:34:38,276 --> 00:34:41,143
We're all responsible
for the choices we make.

469
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:47,215
- Don't you want to be a good person?
- What I want is to be happy.

470
00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:49,810
That's the answer of a selfish child.

471
00:34:51,355 --> 00:34:53,915
I know.

472
00:34:59,330 --> 00:35:02,493
I started taking the pills
because they gave me energy

473
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:07,469
but then I couldn't sleep at night
and I was so tired in the daytime and...

474
00:35:08,573 --> 00:35:11,269
It totally messed me up.

475
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:18,879
I love my kids so much.
I'm so sorry they have me as a mother.

476
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:22,249
Lynette, you're a great mother.

477
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,584
No, I'm not.

478
00:35:24,655 --> 00:35:26,646
I can't do it.

479
00:35:26,724 --> 00:35:30,592
I'm so tired of feeling like a failure.
It's so humiliating.

480
00:35:30,661 --> 00:35:33,357
No, it's not!

481
00:35:33,431 --> 00:35:37,993
So you got addicted to your kids'
A.D.D. Medication. It happens.

482
00:35:38,069 --> 00:35:41,596
You've got four kids. That's a lot
of stress. You just need help.

483
00:35:41,739 --> 00:35:46,301
That's what so humiliating.
Other moms don't need help.

484
00:35:46,377 --> 00:35:50,643
Other moms make it look so easy.
All I do is complain.

485
00:35:50,748 --> 00:35:52,443
That's just not true!

486
00:35:52,517 --> 00:35:56,510
When Julie was a baby,
I was out of my mind almost every day.

487
00:35:56,621 --> 00:35:59,590
I got so upset
when Andrew and Danielle were little,

488
00:35:59,657 --> 00:36:01,359
I used their nap times to cry.

489
00:36:01,359 --> 00:36:01,848
I used their nap times to cry.

490
00:36:05,096 --> 00:36:08,691
Why didn't you ever tell me this?

491
00:36:08,799 --> 00:36:13,827
Oh, baby. Nobody likes to admit
that they can't handle the pressure.

492
00:36:13,905 --> 00:36:19,707
I think it's just like we think, you
know, it's easier to keep it all in.

493
00:36:19,777 --> 00:36:24,976
Oh, we shouldn't!
We should tell each other this stuff!

494
00:36:27,151 --> 00:36:29,779
- It helps, huh?
- Yeah.

495
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:32,516
It really does.

496
00:36:45,136 --> 00:36:47,434
So it was Martha Huber all along.

497
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:52,238
Seems so. Edie didn't move in with Huber
until after your wife received the note.

498
00:36:52,310 --> 00:36:55,074
My God,
we almost killed an innocent woman.

499
00:36:55,179 --> 00:36:57,773
Like I said, I don't do refunds,

500
00:36:57,882 --> 00:37:00,908
but if you like,
I'm willing to pay Mrs. Huber a visit.

501
00:37:01,018 --> 00:37:03,953
No. Just keep the money.

502
00:37:04,021 --> 00:37:09,118
This whole thing's been tearing me up.
The nightmares, the guilt.

503
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:11,787
This isn't what Mary Alice
would have wanted.

504
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:14,558
What would she have wanted?

505
00:37:17,068 --> 00:37:19,127
Answers.

506
00:37:23,541 --> 00:37:26,203
- Hello, Mrs. Huber.
- Paul.

507
00:37:26,277 --> 00:37:28,370
- Let me help.
- That's not necessary.

508
00:37:28,446 --> 00:37:30,277
I insist.

509
00:38:34,412 --> 00:38:36,175
- Ants, huh?
- Yes.

510
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:38,578
I've had a little infestation problem.

511
00:38:38,649 --> 00:38:41,083
I wanted to take care of it
before my trip.

512
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:44,087
Never had a problem with ants.

513
00:38:44,188 --> 00:38:46,884
Mary Alice and I had
these little black flies once.

514
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:49,551
- Oh?
- She was so funny about it.

515
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:54,495
She ran out and bought herself a can
of poison something to spray them down.

516
00:38:54,565 --> 00:38:58,524
So she's taking aim at one
on the counter and she just stops.

517
00:38:58,602 --> 00:39:01,901
Puts the can down. Couldn't do it.

518
00:39:01,972 --> 00:39:05,373
She told me later it felt too personal.

519
00:39:05,476 --> 00:39:08,968
Literally couldn't kill a fly.
That's how gentle she was.

520
00:39:09,046 --> 00:39:11,571
Then you must have lived with
quite a few flies.

521
00:39:11,649 --> 00:39:14,550
I'm going to have to say
good night to you now, Paul.

522
00:39:23,928 --> 00:39:27,261
- What are you doing here?
- I want to know why.

523
00:39:33,437 --> 00:39:35,701
[Knocking]

524
00:39:40,544 --> 00:39:44,446
I know you've got a lot of questions
and I know I don't want to lose you.

525
00:39:44,515 --> 00:39:47,245
So ask me anything you want.

526
00:39:47,318 --> 00:39:50,515
You just told me
everything I need to know.

527
00:39:57,862 --> 00:40:03,858
All right. My idiot husband died
and left me with a worthless pension.

528
00:40:04,001 --> 00:40:05,866
I was desperate for money

529
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:08,769
and I'd rather take it
from a bad person than a good one.

530
00:40:08,873 --> 00:40:12,331
- I didn't know she'd shoot herself.
- She was a good person.

531
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:14,901
A good person
who leaves her child motherless?

532
00:40:14,979 --> 00:40:17,675
Read the Bible. Suicide's a big no-no.

533
00:40:17,815 --> 00:40:20,943
- Don't you feel any remorse?
- Why should I?

534
00:40:21,018 --> 00:40:23,782
Your wife didn't kill herself
because I wrote a note.

535
00:40:23,888 --> 00:40:28,154
She killed herself because
of what she did to that poor baby.

536
00:40:28,225 --> 00:40:32,753
But rest assured
I'm praying for Mary Alice.

537
00:40:32,830 --> 00:40:36,095
After what she did,
she'll need all of our prayers.

538
00:41:25,082 --> 00:41:29,382
There is a widely-read book
that tells us everyone is a sinner.

539
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:39,129
Of course, not everyone fels guilt
over the bad things they do.

540
00:41:40,164 --> 00:41:44,897
In contrast, there are those who assume
more than their share of the blame.

541
00:41:49,573 --> 00:41:53,304
There are others
who soothe their consciences

542
00:41:53,377 --> 00:41:56,471
with small acts of kindness.

543
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:06,981
Or by telling themselves
their sins were justified.

544
00:42:10,728 --> 00:42:15,392
Finally, there are the ones
who simply vow to do better next time,

545
00:42:15,499 --> 00:42:17,990
and pray for forgiveness.

546
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:33,675
Sometimes, their prayers are answered.

